## Fix Management Analysis

### What it is

Ad-hoc analysis of ~1,180 LPP Fix Management tickets (2024 Q1‚Äì2026 Q1), where customer hotfixes conflict with internal LPD fixes. Volume grew ~25x (48 tickets Q1 2024 ‚Üí 1,208 Q1 2026).

### Files

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `FixManagementAnalysis.R` | Full pipeline ‚Äî Jira fetch, plots, LDA, TF-IDF, CSV/RData export |
| `FixManagementDashboard.Rmd` | Shiny flexdashboard, loads from RData (intentional split ‚Äî avoids re-fetching) |
| `output/fixmgmt_dashboard.RData` | Pre-computed R objects |
| `output/raw_issues_cache.rds` | Cached Jira response ‚Äî re-run from section 2 without re-fetching |
| `export_fixmgmt.R` | Writes CSVs to `output/looker/fixmgmt/` |

### Conflict data for RAP

- File: `output/tables/component_freq.csv`
- Columns: `value`, `n`
- Filter rows containing `>` AND starting with `~`

### Top findings

- **LPD-64813 / LPD-64812 / LPD-64131** ‚Äî highest-priority cluster; co-occur on most tickets; 7 customers √ó 6 versions; must be backported as an atomic unit
- **Objects component** ‚Äî structural conflict (field/relationship/localized changes), not individual bugs; requires architectural intervention
- **Core Infrastructure** ‚Äî security-driven (CVE), non-discretionary; needs dedicated capacity
- **Web Content** ‚Äî driven by LPD-57453 and LPD-48888; two bugs, high spread

### Analytical method notes

- **TF-IDF:** `LPD-XXXXX` tokens are ticket IDs ‚Äî do NOT remove, they are valid component-LPD association signals
- **LDA:** `removeNumbers` strips IDs from topics (intentional); terms are stemmed
- **LDA topics (6):** patch/upgrade, security/localization, UI customization, patcher builds, web content rebases, LPE/catalog
- **LPD Spread bubble chart:** lines are ggrepel label arrows, not data relationships; X = version reach, Y = customer reach, size = ticket count
- **Docker:** `setwd` in Rmd setup chunk must be wrapped in `dir.exists()` guard or `try()` ‚Äî else crash

